To be more specific, to provide equity release advice, the adviser must:

(a) have a CEIAPS (Certificate in Equity Release) or equivalent qualification;
(b) have completed relevant CPD (Continuing Professional Development);
(c) have access to a wide range of equity release products from different providers; and,
(d) provide a balanced market view when advising clients.

To be specific, Rule 13 in MCOB states:

"A firm must not provide advice on an equity release transaction unless it has ensured that the customer has received a personalized recommendation that takes into account at least the following factors:

(1) the customer's requirements and objectives;
(2) the customer's financial situation;
(3) the customer's knowledge and experience;
(4) the customer's attitude to risk; and 
(5) the customer's capacity for loss."
